1
00:00:31,816 --> 00:00:33,969
What the hell are you doing?

2
00:00:34,470 --> 00:00:36,083
You pervert!

3
00:00:36,330 --> 00:00:37,663
I'm sorry.

4
00:00:38,821 --> 00:00:40,579
But please.

5
00:00:40,619 --> 00:00:42,030
- Huh?
- Please.

6
00:00:42,070 --> 00:00:43,992
- What?!
- Please, please, let me!

7
00:00:44,032 --> 00:00:46,697
Stop— Stop it!

8
00:00:46,737 --> 00:00:49,605
Sto— Stop! You bastard!

9
00:00:50,956 --> 00:00:52,176
I'm sorry.

10
00:00:52,746 --> 00:00:55,192
B-But I just...

11
00:00:55,378 --> 00:00:57,478
Don't "but" me!

12
00:00:57,518 --> 00:01:00,068
This is an actual crime, jerk!

13
00:01:19,330 --> 00:01:21,916
Alright!

14
00:01:24,642 --> 00:01:26,169
Ta-da!

15
00:01:26,508 --> 00:01:28,302
Yay!

16
00:01:28,342 --> 00:01:30,048
Thank you!

17
00:01:32,715 --> 00:01:34,229
Here we go!

18
00:01:41,506 --> 00:01:44,906
- Shall we have some action tonight?
- I'm so glad to be alive!

19
00:02:11,405 --> 00:02:14,379
I Still Want to Do It with My Wife

20
00:02:14,852 --> 00:02:20,085
Episode 6: Lonely in Body and Mind

21
00:02:23,212 --> 00:02:24,952
About yesterday.

22
00:02:25,606 --> 00:02:27,046
I'm really sorry.

23
00:02:27,923 --> 00:02:29,123
I was...

24
00:02:30,095 --> 00:02:31,500
a little out of my mind.

25
00:02:31,540 --> 00:02:33,338
"A little"? Like hell.

26
00:02:33,693 --> 00:02:35,925
Don't talk to me, you creep.

27
00:02:51,101 --> 00:02:53,294
Seriously, what do I do?

28
00:02:53,388 --> 00:02:55,334
I can't forgive him at all.

29
00:02:55,467 --> 00:02:58,480
I'm so miserable I called my parents,
which I never do.

30
00:02:58,558 --> 00:03:00,185
My tears just keep falling,

31
00:03:00,225 --> 00:03:03,019
and though it's pointless,
I keep thinking about it.

32
00:03:03,247 --> 00:03:04,967
I seriously wanna kill him.

33
00:03:05,827 --> 00:03:08,420
I mean, I told him to drop dead,

34
00:03:08,460 --> 00:03:10,917
and he just casually told me he can't.

35
00:03:10,957 --> 00:03:13,577
He said, "If you'll forgive me,
I'll come back home."

36
00:03:13,617 --> 00:03:16,370
"But if you won't,
I'll have to start a new life."

37
00:03:16,410 --> 00:03:18,328
All calm and collected the whole time.

38
00:03:18,368 --> 00:03:20,614
That side of him really pisses me off.

39
00:03:23,154 --> 00:03:24,548
Hey, are you listening?

40
00:03:24,706 --> 00:03:25,746
Huh?

41
00:03:25,786 --> 00:03:27,240
Like I said,

42
00:03:27,259 --> 00:03:31,285
He's seriously a lost cause,
so I'm already planning how to move on.

43
00:03:31,753 --> 00:03:34,159
I was literally looking at the dark web,

44
00:03:34,406 --> 00:03:36,106
thinking I'd kill him.

45
00:03:37,505 --> 00:03:39,896
But if he dies easily,
it won't satisfy my anger,

46
00:03:39,936 --> 00:03:42,121
so I want him to suffer hard.

47
00:03:42,161 --> 00:03:44,248
And his mistress should suffer with him.

48
00:03:44,288 --> 00:03:47,174
I'd spare her family,
but they should suffer, too.

49
00:04:44,750 --> 00:04:46,343
Morning.

50
00:04:47,253 --> 00:04:48,605
You're up early.

51
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:51,557
I'm doing
your
work, dumbass.

52
00:04:51,903 --> 00:04:53,890
Hurry up and make breakfast.

53
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:55,625
Oh, okay.

54
00:04:57,768 --> 00:04:59,268
Thanks.

55
00:05:01,232 --> 00:05:02,432
Get lost.

56
00:05:19,876 --> 00:05:21,089
There you go.

57
00:05:21,150 --> 00:05:24,256
I wrote part of it. Read it over.
It's the story's plot.

58
00:05:26,035 --> 00:05:27,363
Thanks.

59
00:05:28,390 --> 00:05:30,150
I'm doing it all in the end.

60
00:05:30,983 --> 00:05:33,443
Seriously, thank you so much.

61
00:05:35,156 --> 00:05:37,533
Nishimura wants to meet again today,

62
00:05:37,573 --> 00:05:40,068
so I'll go after work.

63
00:05:40,338 --> 00:05:43,069
Huh? Today as well?

64
00:05:43,149 --> 00:05:45,743
Don't "huh" me. It can't be helped.

65
00:05:45,783 --> 00:05:48,870
- You're gonna drink again?
- How should I know?

66
00:05:50,470 --> 00:05:51,862
I'm going with you.

67
00:05:52,273 --> 00:05:53,628
What are you saying?

68
00:05:53,790 --> 00:05:57,271
Then
you
go. No need for two people.
Who would watch Taro?

69
00:05:57,311 --> 00:06:00,611
But this is
my
job.

70
00:06:01,110 --> 00:06:02,715
What are you talking about?

71
00:06:02,789 --> 00:06:05,286
Then do it yourself from the start.

72
00:06:06,772 --> 00:06:08,470
Go to the meeting yourself.

73
00:06:11,399 --> 00:06:12,466
Huh?

74
00:06:12,506 --> 00:06:14,440
What is it? You can't go?

75
00:06:15,047 --> 00:06:16,928
Well, of course you can't.

76
00:06:16,968 --> 00:06:21,348
Because you don't know a damn thing.
Maybe try begging them to teach you.

77
00:06:24,269 --> 00:06:27,355
So what's it gonna be? Decide who's going.

78
00:06:27,509 --> 00:06:30,060
You pathetic weakling, blinded by jealousy.

79
00:06:32,212 --> 00:06:36,432
Okay, fine. Then I'll go myself.

80
00:06:36,943 --> 00:06:42,674
Also, I glanced at the plot you've written.
It's total garbage.

81
00:06:42,747 --> 00:06:46,440
What did you glance at?
I just handed it to you a minute ago.

82
00:06:46,895 --> 00:06:49,678
All you're good at is being a jealous loser.

83
00:06:49,718 --> 00:06:52,002
Can't stand me being
alone with Nishimura, right?

84
00:06:52,042 --> 00:06:54,597
- Whatever. Do what you want.
- You know...

85
00:06:54,982 --> 00:06:59,129
Nishimura doesn't actually
think things through.

86
00:06:59,164 --> 00:07:01,050
He just wants to see you.

87
00:07:01,090 --> 00:07:05,008
What? Is it wrong to be jealous?
Anyone would be.

88
00:07:05,043 --> 00:07:08,314
That guy looks down on me.

89
00:07:08,830 --> 00:07:12,041
I'm simply not good at
writing this kind of stuff.

90
00:07:12,418 --> 00:07:15,651
I didn't even want this job.

91
00:07:15,895 --> 00:07:18,838
You're the one who wanted
the money, right?

92
00:07:19,025 --> 00:07:23,146
You wanted the money,
so you've been telling me to sell my soul.

93
00:07:23,329 --> 00:07:27,189
I've been selling my soul left and right.
That's why it's come to this!

94
00:07:27,194 --> 00:07:30,314
I should've never taken
this job in the first place.

95
00:07:35,168 --> 00:07:38,281
You're finished. Get out.

96
00:07:39,134 --> 00:07:43,401
You don't actually feel bad
about the assault or the groping, do you?

97
00:07:50,142 --> 00:07:55,268
Why are you being so loud this early?
This is why I don't wanna go to school.

98
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:58,107
I told you to close the bathroom door.

99
00:07:59,590 --> 00:08:03,266
Daddy's gonna go for a little walk, okay?

100
00:08:14,590 --> 00:08:19,777
I know better than anyone that there's
no point in me going to the meeting.

101
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:34,652
I'm sorry about this morning.

102
00:08:34,692 --> 00:08:40,292
I wasn't thinking straight.

103
00:08:43,349 --> 00:08:45,629
Wait, used that phrase already.

104
00:08:46,367 --> 00:08:47,881
I'm hungry.

105
00:08:48,173 --> 00:08:49,373
Hold on a bit.

106
00:08:50,435 --> 00:08:53,161
- What about lunch?
- Hold on a bit.

107
00:08:54,540 --> 00:08:59,463
You're right, Chika. There's no point
in me going to the meeting.

108
00:08:59,513 --> 00:09:05,022
I said nonsensical things
out of petty jealousy. I'm truly sorry.

109
00:09:07,100 --> 00:09:10,550
The meeting with Nishimura is
at the company where Yoyogi works.

110
00:09:10,735 --> 00:09:14,022
It was scheduled for after my work,
so it's at 6 pm.

111
00:09:14,312 --> 00:09:19,260
I've already told them you're going,
so you'd better go. Don't you dare run.

112
00:09:26,366 --> 00:09:31,393
I've been thinking, and it really would be
faster if you went instead, Chika.

113
00:09:31,610 --> 00:09:34,567
I'm truly sorry about this morning.

114
00:09:39,730 --> 00:09:42,105
Read

115
00:09:44,754 --> 00:09:47,521
I'm absolutely not going.

116
00:09:51,256 --> 00:09:53,955
- I'm hungry.
- Hold on a bit.

117
00:09:54,827 --> 00:09:56,214
What do you wanna eat?

118
00:09:56,367 --> 00:09:57,380
Fried rice?

119
00:09:57,420 --> 00:09:58,987
- Fried rice.
- Okay.

120
00:10:08,490 --> 00:10:14,455
If you could be Shohei Ohtani for one day,
what would you do? I'd probably—

121
00:10:14,495 --> 00:10:16,036
Oh, here he comes.

122
00:10:18,846 --> 00:10:20,354
How's your wife?

123
00:10:21,587 --> 00:10:22,980
What do you mean?

124
00:10:23,211 --> 00:10:26,364
I heard you two had quite the fight.

125
00:10:26,617 --> 00:10:29,063
She said you got jealous of this guy.

126
00:10:29,645 --> 00:10:31,690
No way, what's that about?

127
00:10:31,730 --> 00:10:36,065
Sorry, maybe it was my fault
for keeping her out late last time.

128
00:10:36,481 --> 00:10:39,311
You insisted on coming yourself today, right?

129
00:10:39,495 --> 00:10:42,068
Nishimura got a message from your wife.

130
00:10:42,367 --> 00:10:44,527
- Wanna read it?
- No, it's fine.

131
00:10:44,567 --> 00:10:49,107
I couldn't make it last time,
so I just figured I'd come today.

132
00:10:49,147 --> 00:10:53,674
But your wife wrote it again, right?
Seriously! It's totally obvious.

133
00:10:53,746 --> 00:10:57,306
But we got a great plot
from her this morning.

134
00:10:57,313 --> 00:11:02,788
After reading it, I got some ideas,
so I messaged her to see if we could meet.

135
00:11:02,828 --> 00:11:04,362
Sorry about that.

136
00:11:04,660 --> 00:11:09,087
But at this point, even he can
handle the rest, right?

137
00:11:09,127 --> 00:11:10,587
Well, I suppose so.

138
00:11:10,643 --> 00:11:15,253
Hey, saying "even he" is kind of rude,
don't you think?

139
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:17,795
But she really is
a wonderful wife, isn't she?

140
00:11:18,109 --> 00:11:23,409
"My husband doesn't understand the illness,
so please explain it to him properly."

141
00:11:23,453 --> 00:11:28,135
She says, "He's an idiot," but it's obvious
she can't give up on him, though.

142
00:11:28,780 --> 00:11:30,140
Oh, sorry, sorry!

143
00:11:31,629 --> 00:11:36,642
I get why you'd be jealous. She's charming.

144
00:11:36,973 --> 00:11:38,853
You think so?

145
00:11:39,663 --> 00:11:43,185
I can't stand her. She's way too pushy.

146
00:11:56,141 --> 00:11:57,370
I'm home.

147
00:13:20,964 --> 00:13:22,164
Morning.

148
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:23,520
Were you pooping?

149
00:13:27,913 --> 00:13:29,243
Hey...

150
00:13:30,696 --> 00:13:35,270
I'm really sorry. About yesterday.

151
00:13:39,102 --> 00:13:42,078
Oh, I went to the meeting.

152
00:13:42,118 --> 00:13:43,326
Listen.

153
00:13:43,818 --> 00:13:45,859
I don't wanna talk to you.

154
00:13:51,526 --> 00:13:53,025
What's your problem?

155
00:13:53,435 --> 00:13:56,322
Acting like nothing happened,
just chatting me up.

156
00:13:57,094 --> 00:14:00,474
I am seriously disgusted with you.

157
00:14:02,106 --> 00:14:03,486
Don't come near me.

158
00:14:08,378 --> 00:14:11,110
It sounds like you're just
bragging about your wife.

159
00:14:11,150 --> 00:14:12,400
Wait, does it?

160
00:14:12,440 --> 00:14:15,973
I mean, she asked that director
to look after you, right?

161
00:14:16,013 --> 00:14:18,863
She's a great wife,
just like the director said.

162
00:14:18,903 --> 00:14:20,908
Are you bragging? Is that what this is?

163
00:14:20,948 --> 00:14:23,140
No, this isn't bragging.

164
00:14:23,180 --> 00:14:26,365
Everything sounds like bragging
to me right now.

165
00:14:26,405 --> 00:14:29,772
If you just wanna gush about her,
don't drag me out here.

166
00:14:29,926 --> 00:14:32,946
I'm seriously struggling here.

167
00:14:33,512 --> 00:14:37,592
What Chika's most angry about is probably...

168
00:14:38,254 --> 00:14:41,768
that I tried to force myself on her,

169
00:14:42,501 --> 00:14:45,281
or that I started spouting nonsense
out of jealousy.

170
00:14:45,898 --> 00:14:51,849
I don't even know how to apologize.
She won't listen to a word I say.

171
00:14:51,889 --> 00:14:54,340
Turn yourself in.
You forced yourself on her, right?

172
00:14:54,380 --> 00:14:57,676
- Come on, don't joke about that.
- I'm not joking.

173
00:15:01,953 --> 00:15:06,297
I admit I was ignorant
about that stuff, but...

174
00:15:06,337 --> 00:15:12,200
But Midori, you were the one saying
Chika might be having an affair.

175
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:16,103
What? You're blaming me?
Is that why you forced yourself on her?

176
00:15:18,689 --> 00:15:21,879
That's exactly why Chika gets mad at you.

177
00:15:21,962 --> 00:15:26,038
You're petty, always trying shift
the blame onto other people.

178
00:15:26,078 --> 00:15:27,644
Am I right, Go?

179
00:15:28,310 --> 00:15:30,230
And she sees right through it.

180
00:15:31,998 --> 00:15:37,150
Anyway, I've got my own problems.
I can't sit here listening to your love life.

181
00:15:37,190 --> 00:15:42,847
The other day, I swallowed my pride
and begged him to hold me, and he refused.

182
00:15:44,670 --> 00:15:50,133
Just shook his head and said, "No can do."
That man has no heart.

183
00:15:51,449 --> 00:15:54,880
- You became "it" in hide-and-seek, right?
- Yeah.

184
00:15:54,920 --> 00:15:57,589
How did that make you feel?

185
00:15:57,950 --> 00:15:59,808
- Huh?
- How did you feel?

186
00:15:59,905 --> 00:16:02,870
Hmm... I didn't like it.

187
00:16:02,910 --> 00:16:06,733
You didn't? Then put the sad face
down here. Put it down.

188
00:16:07,329 --> 00:16:11,935
But if there's no seeker in hide-and-seek,
that'd be a problem, right?

189
00:16:11,975 --> 00:16:13,672
It wouldn't be hide-and-seek.

190
00:16:13,712 --> 00:16:15,470
Yeah, but it's not a problem.

191
00:16:15,510 --> 00:16:17,574
- Yes, it is.
- No, it's not. It's not.

192
00:16:17,614 --> 00:16:19,151
Then who will do the seeking?

193
00:16:19,191 --> 00:16:20,971
Someone else will.

194
00:16:32,088 --> 00:16:35,770
Hey, can we talk for a sec?

195
00:16:36,380 --> 00:16:37,705
I have nothing to say.

196
00:16:38,187 --> 00:16:42,055
No, it'd be a serious conversation.

197
00:16:46,066 --> 00:16:53,866
Look... I'm really sorry. For everything.

198
00:16:54,388 --> 00:16:59,021
I said I don't wanna talk, and you
just force it anyway. I despise that.

199
00:17:00,726 --> 00:17:05,428
Sorry. Um, well then...

200
00:17:06,785 --> 00:17:12,147
After I put Taro to bed,
please give me just a moment.

201
00:17:15,135 --> 00:17:16,403
Please.

202
00:17:20,512 --> 00:17:21,712
Well then...

203
00:17:55,269 --> 00:17:59,941
Um, Taro's asleep now.

204
00:18:00,475 --> 00:18:02,942
I want to read the paper.

205
00:18:03,846 --> 00:18:10,168
Sorry. I'll... try to keep it brief.

206
00:18:11,494 --> 00:18:15,211
Cut the creepy polite talk.
It makes me sick.

207
00:18:15,541 --> 00:18:18,430
Your true self is what you were
yesterday morning.

208
00:18:18,909 --> 00:18:22,663
I've been selling my soul left and right.
That's why it's come to this!

209
00:18:24,036 --> 00:18:25,236
Right.

210
00:18:27,870 --> 00:18:30,662
- Don't "right" me. You don't get it.
- I do get it.

211
00:18:30,702 --> 00:18:32,493
No, you don't.

212
00:18:33,290 --> 00:18:36,799
You always pull that crap
when you get jealous and freak out.

213
00:18:37,113 --> 00:18:38,420
So damn lame.

214
00:18:38,596 --> 00:18:40,067
Gross, lame, pathetic.

215
00:18:40,499 --> 00:18:41,705
Yeah.

216
00:18:42,410 --> 00:18:49,533
So, I wanted to properly apologize
for all of that, too.

217
00:18:51,894 --> 00:18:58,334
Actually, Midori's been coming
to me for advice recently.

218
00:18:58,572 --> 00:18:59,778
Um,

219
00:19:01,850 --> 00:19:04,278
Mina's dad is having an affair, apparently.

220
00:19:05,042 --> 00:19:09,332
Huh? What's that about? I don't care.
It's got nothing to do with us.

221
00:19:09,372 --> 00:19:12,038
Yeah, it doesn't, I know, but...

222
00:19:12,180 --> 00:19:15,799
But I'm an idiot, so...

223
00:19:16,384 --> 00:19:22,008
I started imagining stupid things,
like you and Nishimura having an affair.

224
00:19:22,372 --> 00:19:24,959
And I also got turned on.

225
00:19:25,479 --> 00:19:27,072
So that's why I...

226
00:19:29,205 --> 00:19:31,300
What's your point?

227
00:19:32,215 --> 00:19:33,853
God, you're gross.

228
00:19:33,946 --> 00:19:37,455
I've gotta do
your
work after this,
so hurry it up.

229
00:19:37,495 --> 00:19:38,697
Okay...

230
00:19:39,530 --> 00:19:42,234
So what I'm trying to say is,

231
00:19:46,226 --> 00:19:49,328
it all started from my jealousy.

232
00:19:50,138 --> 00:19:54,416
I'm really sorry about everything.

233
00:19:54,970 --> 00:19:58,261
- I thought it over.
- Yeah, do that for the next decade.

234
00:19:58,416 --> 00:19:59,616
Yes.

235
00:20:05,369 --> 00:20:10,208
But still, for me...

236
00:20:17,013 --> 00:20:21,099
not doing it at all is lonely.

237
00:20:25,346 --> 00:20:27,586
It always comes back to that.

238
00:20:28,733 --> 00:20:33,124
I want to touch you, hold you.

239
00:20:37,203 --> 00:20:40,525
Not having any of that...

240
00:20:41,340 --> 00:20:42,664
It feels like...

241
00:20:44,203 --> 00:20:49,160
my body and mind... are both falling apart.

242
00:20:49,971 --> 00:20:55,642
I know doing it isn't the only way
to feel that connection, but...

243
00:20:57,239 --> 00:20:58,656
But...

244
00:21:02,341 --> 00:21:03,968
I'm lonely.

245
00:21:06,100 --> 00:21:07,605
I want to believe

246
00:21:10,662 --> 00:21:13,020
we still love each other.

247
00:21:15,826 --> 00:21:17,105
So...

248
00:21:19,884 --> 00:21:22,197
I'd like to do it with you

249
00:21:25,808 --> 00:21:27,721
at least once a month.

250
00:21:36,135 --> 00:21:37,595
So, I was thinking...

251
00:21:38,368 --> 00:21:39,642
Yes?

252
00:21:42,813 --> 00:21:46,557
Couldn't we keep our marriage
going without sex?

253
00:21:57,060 --> 00:22:01,784
What came out of Chika's mouth
was completely unexpected.

254
00:22:02,381 --> 00:22:06,701
Somehow, I had this naive hope in my mind

255
00:22:06,741 --> 00:22:13,061
that she might say something,
like "Fine, I guess we can do it."

256
00:22:14,900 --> 00:22:15,900
Next Episode Preview

257
00:22:15,927 --> 00:22:19,000
You sure? If your wife
finds out, you're in big trouble.

258
00:22:19,040 --> 00:22:20,842
She's cool with brothels.

259
00:22:20,891 --> 00:22:23,522
You have zero appeal right now.

260
00:22:23,705 --> 00:22:25,816
What even is love?

261
00:22:25,856 --> 00:22:28,553
Why don't you get a divorce?

262
00:22:28,632 --> 00:22:29,832
Huh?
